Given a positive integer N, write a program to count the number of digits in N.
Input Format

A single integer N
Constraints

-10^9 <= N <= 10^9
Output Format

Print the count of digits in the absolute value of N.
Sample Input 0

-12345
Sample Output 0

5
Sample Input 1

756
Sample Output 1

3

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        int c=0;
        if(n==0){
            c=1;
        }else{
            while(n!=0){
                c++;
                n=n/10;
            }
        }
        System.out.println(c);
    }
}
